{
  "texts": [
    "To address this issue, pioneering work has begun to integrate fault-aware techniques into the generation process.",
    "For example, MuTAP [32] leverages mutation testing, feeding surviving mutants back to the LLM to guide the creation of semantically stronger test cases.",
    "However, we argue that a fundamental paradigm shift is needed, moving from implementation-based test generation to specification-driven test generation, to decouple the process from potentially faulty source code.Incorrect Test Oracles.",
    "This represents a fundamental challenge directly affecting fault detection, as an incorrect assertion can lead to both false positives (failing on correct code) and false negatives (passing on faulty code).",
    "The accuracy of test oracles is directly limited by the shortcomings of LLMs in precise calculation and logical reasoning."
  ]
}